clinical_history: Routine obstetric ultrasound for fetal growth.
findings: Liver appears hyperechoic with no focal lesions.
Fetal cardiac activity present with FHR 1.11 bpm.
Testes are hypoechoic with normal vascularity.
Uterus appears mildly thickened; endometrial thickness measures 11.13 mm.
Urinary bladder is well-defined, no intraluminal lesions.
Prostate is well-defined; volume approximately 26.51 cc.
Gallbladder shows mildly heterogeneous, no stones or wall thickening.
Major vessels show enlarged waveform on Doppler.
